webLinks.linkText: Wallaga Lake Bridge essential maintenance work

properties.otherAdvice:
WALLAGA LAKE BRIDGE ESSENTIAL MAINTENANCE WORK

The bridge will remain open to traffic as early work begins, including setting up the site compound and receiving deliveries.

Motorists may experience a 5 minute delay at times.

The first full closure of the bridge will commence on 29 April 2024.

Standard construction hours are:

Weekdays - 7am to 6pm

Saturdays - 8am to 5pm

Sundays - 8am to 1pm

KEY DATES

Monday 29 April - Bridge closed for four weeks

Monday 27 May - The bridge re-opens under traffic control for six weeks

Monday 8 July - Bridge closing for three weeks

Monday 29 July - The bridge re-opens under traffic control for five weeks while finishing work is completed

Traffic controllers will be on site to direct motorists. Motorists are advised to allow approximately 5 minutes of additional travel time.

Northbound and southbound speed limit outside of work hours on the Pacific Highway between Masonite Road and Mount Hall Road is reduced from 110km/h to 80km/h until the 30 June 2025.

properties.otherAdvice:
EMERGENCY WORK DUE TO WEATHER - Urgent drainage and road pavement repairs will be carried out on 8, 9 & 12 May between 8pm & 5am on Maitland Road between the Newcastle Inner City Bypass and Shamrock Street and between Old Maitland Road and Hexham Bowling Club. Shoulder and closures: on outbound lanes towards Maitland between Newcastle Inner City Bypass and Shamrock Street and on inbound lanes towards Newcastle Hexham Station and Old Maitland Road, Hexham.

From Sunday 5 May, night works will also be undertaken on Maitland Road between Hexham Train Station and the Oak Factory at Hexham. Contra-flow arrangements will be in place and may add an additional 15 minutes to travel time. This work will continue over four weeks, weather permitting. A temporary speed of 60km/h will remain in place through the project work zone during ongoing day work, and a reduction to 40km/h during night works. 

Significant restrictions for over size and over mass vehicles with ground contact wider than 3.2m will be in place during the work. Permitholders are required to contact the project team on 1800 515 141 to plan times and movements through or around the works.
The Sydney Harbour Tunnel and Eastern Distributor will also be closed.
